cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on device-to-device communication in cellular networks and evaluates network performance using stochastic geometry. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses cognitive access protocols and the impact of physical layer features on system performance. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper models the service queueing process and traffic dynamics. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch upon security concerns related to cache-enabled D2D communication. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also less likely but possible as the paper investigates the impact of content-centric features on system performance.
